.TH "alloc_dma_desc_resources" 9 "alloc_dma_desc_resources" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_dma_desc_resources \- alloc TX/RX resources.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" alloc_dma_desc_resources
.BI "(struct stmmac_priv *priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "priv" 12
private structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
according to which descriptor can be used (extend or basic)
this function allocates the resources for TX and RX paths. In case of
reception, for example, it pre-allocated the RX socket buffer in order to
allow zero-copy mechanism.
